Its been a while since I posted but I wanted to share this dish that I didnt get to try while in Korea but did taste at anjufrc while visiting my brother in DC This particular version is my take on gungjung tteokbokki or royal court tteokbokki a less spicy soy sauce based tteokbokki usually made with stir fried beef Because hubby doesnt eat beef I used thinly sliced pork shoulderbutt instead which worked just as well in the recipe And though I did say that this is a less spicy version I couldnt resist adding some red and green Korean peppers as well as a few healthy shakes of black pepper I also added some shimeji mushrooms thinly sliced onions and carrots If you like tteok rice cakes this is a great recipe to try
